@permcody

I am setting up some kernels for a FV problem. In one kernel, I need to access materials properties for a volume contribution to the residual. So I have InputParameters:
InputParameters
MyFVVolumeKernel::validParams()
{
InputParameters params = FVElementalKernel::validParams();
..
params.addRequired<MooseFunctorName>("Km", "materials property");
....
return params;
}

and later

MyFVVolumeKernel::MyFVVolumeKernel(const inputParameters & parameters):FVElementalKernel(parameters),
...
_Km(getFunctor<ADRreal>("Km"),
..

and for the residual
ADReal
MyFVVolumeKernel::computeQPResidual()
{
return _Km[_qp]*u[_qp];
}

The problem I have seems to be that I cannot evaluate _Km at quadrature points - the error when I compile is
"no match for 'operator[]'"
How can I fix this?
Thanks!
